# Icon Usage Guidelines

Always use FontAwesome icons as the primary icon library. When an icon is not available in FontAwesome, create custom SVG icons.

## FontAwesome First

```blade
{{-- ✅ GOOD - Use FontAwesome classes --}}
<i class="fas fa-home"></i>
<i class="far fa-user"></i>
<i class="fab fa-github"></i>

{{-- Use with Tailwind classes for styling --}}
<i class="fas fa-check text-green-500 text-xl"></i>
<i class="fas fa-times text-red-500 text-2xl"></i>
```

## Custom SVGs When Needed

```blade
{{-- ✅ GOOD - Custom SVG when FontAwesome doesn't have it --}}
<svg class="w-6 h-6" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
    <path d="M12 2L2 7v10c0 5.55 3.84 10.74 9 12 5.16-1.26 9-6.45 9-12V7l-10-5z"/>
</svg>

{{-- Store reusable custom SVGs as Blade components --}}
{{-- resources/views/components/icons/custom-bee.blade.php --}}
<x-icons.custom-bee class="w-8 h-8 text-yellow-500" />
```

## Best Practices

- Use semantic icon names that match their purpose
- Apply consistent sizing using Tailwind classes (`text-xl`, `text-2xl`, `w-6 h-6`)
- Use `currentColor` for SVG fill to allow easy color customization
- Create Blade components for frequently used custom SVGs
- Keep SVGs optimized and minimal
